Overview
This project demonstrates the deployment of a Hugging Face model (distilgpt2) to AWS SageMaker and provides scripts for invoking the deployed endpoint, setting up AWS resources, and cleaning up the deployment.

Project Structure
.env
app/
    __init__.py
    config.py
    test_script.py
deploy/
    __init__.py
    aws_setup.py
    clean_up.py
    sagemaker_deploy.py
model/
    code/
        inference.py
        requirements.txt
requirements.txt

Setup
1. Install dependencies:
    pip install -r requirements.txt
2. Environment Variables: Create a .env file in the root directory with the following content:
    AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=<your-aws-access-key-id>
    AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=<your-aws-secret-access-key>
    REGION=us-west-2
    SAGEMAKER_ENDPOINT_NAME=distilgpt2
    MODEL_ID=distilbert/distilgpt2


Scripts
1. app/config.py
This file contains the configuration settings for the project, including AWS credentials and SageMaker endpoint details.

2. app/test_script.py
This script invokes the SageMaker endpoint with a given prompt and prints the generated text.

Usage:
python app/test_script.py

4. clean_up.py
This script deletes the SageMaker endpoint.

Usage:
python deploy/clean_up.py

5. sagemaker_deploy.py
This script deploys the Hugging Face model to SageMaker.

Usage:
python deploy/sagemaker_deploy.py

6. inference.py
This script contains the inference logic for the deployed model, including functions for loading the model, making predictions, and handling input/output.

Requirements
The requirements.txt file contains all the dependencies required for the project.



